<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-20T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1177: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-20T19:00:00-04:00">June 20, 1930—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>204. Your 451, June 17, 1 p.m., last sentence.<note n="45" xml:id="d124fn45">Not printed.</note> The Department assumes that
                            the Legation has at all times in mind possible necessity for the issuing
                            of instructions to consular officers in China or for requesting the
                            despatch of naval vessels with a view to providing for the safety and
                            well-being of American consular officials and other American citizens.
                            Please keep the Department fully informed in this regard.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>